title: I'm Already Level 30
body: Everytime I try to upvote a post, it says that I need to be lvl 30, which I am. Rito what is happening?

replies.body:
There's also this tool my eyes just laid upon:
https://boards.na.leagueoflegends.com/en/c/help-support/fos1aFEB-boards-profile-syncing-tool

This might be the solution to your problem, actually.

Every once and awhile someone's boards profile won't automatically sync up with your summoner level like it's supposed to. In those cases, you just need to post here in H&S or use the Syncing Tool found at the top of H&S.

Not a Riot member, but maybe you could try emptying your cache? It might be that the level data is stored locally, and something fucked up so it still thinks you're not level 30. Ofcourse this only applies if you were on the forums before getting level 30. If not, I have no idea.

Good luck with your issue in any case!
How do I empty the cache?

If it doesn't help, this thread here might be related:
https://boards.na.leagueoflegends.com/en/c/help-support/0doY2Gdi-cant-acess-player-recruitment-to-make-a-discussion
